article.headline: Colgate 70, Cornell 56
article.story: HAMILTON, N.Y. (AP) -- Andrew Zidar tallied 16 points to lead Colgate to a 70-56 win over Cornell Tuesday night. Also in double figures for Colgate (1-2) were Jon Foss with a career-high 14 and Alvin Reed with 11. Keith Williams added seven points and a game-high nine rebounds for the Raiders. Cornell (0-3) was led by Lenny Collins with 13 points, while Cody Toppert had 11 and Ryan Rourke added 10. After Cornell took the early lead, Colgate came back and was up by nine with 2:12 remaining in the first half. The Raiders led 27-23 at halftime. Cornell tied the game 33-33 in the second half, but Colgate went on an 11-2 run to take control. It was Colgate's fourth straight win against Cornell.
